{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17611621","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17611621"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:13:52+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:13:52+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16232"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16232","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16232"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.1,0.57,0.14,0.19]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8923"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75654"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8923","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8923"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16232"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61172"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2044"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5365"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"11707"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21236"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21240"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75654","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75654"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Breast Imaging-Reporting and Data System (BI-RADS) is a system used to standardise the way breast images are reported. It can be applied to mammography, MRI, and ultrasound. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes what is meant when breast tissue is described as category D in breast mammography?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Extremely dense breast tissue, which has no impact on the sensitivity of mammography","Predominantly fatty with isolated areas of density, which decreases the sensitivity of mammography","Extremely dense breast tissue, which decreases the sensitivity of mammography","Suspicious for malignancy, with no impact on the sensitivity of mammography","Highly suggestive of malignancy, with no impact on the sensitivity of mammography"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Breast Imaging-Reporting and Data System (BI-RADS) rovides a structured way to describe number of features of breast imaging such as as breast density, which are relevant to their interpretation. Image findings are synthesised and given a numerical BI-RADS category (0-6), which reflects the likelihood of malignancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe BI-RADS system also includes a categorisation of breast composition (A-D) to describe the relative amounts of fibroglandular and fatty tissue seen on mammography. This is important because dense breast tissue can mask potential abnormalities and affect the sensitivity of mammography.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtremely dense breast tissue, which decreases the sensitivity of mammography\u003C/strong\u003E is correct, with category A breasts being the least dense and category D being the most dense in the BI-RADS categorisation. The density does decrease the sensitivity of mammography, as it is more challenging to detect masses or calcifications. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPredominantly fatty with isolated areas of density\u003C/strong\u003E would be more consistent with category B breast composition rather than category D.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe likelihood of malignancy is reflected by numerical categorisation from 0-6, which explains why the last two options are incorrect. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["BI-RADS breast composition categories describe the relative amounts of fibroglandular and fatty tissue on mammography, and are categorised from A to D.","Category D (extremely dense) breasts significantly reduce mammographic sensitivity for cancer detection","Dense breast tissue appears white on mammography, similar to masses and calcifications"],"references":["D\u2019Orsi CJ, Sickles EA, Mendelson EB, Morris EA, et al. ACR BI-RADS\u00ae Atlas, Breast Imaging Reporting and Data System. Reston, VA, American College of Radiology; 2013","Magny SJ, Shikhman R, Keppke AL. Breast Imaging Reporting and Data System. [Updated 2023 Aug 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459169/?report=classic"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61172"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16232"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61172","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61172"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-30T13:10:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-30T13:11:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8923"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75654"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\u200d\u2620\ufe0f","name":"Radiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"creat